&gt; Hi Chase,
&gt;
&gt; The crawler beans look okay, so it could be that the correct exchange 
&gt; and/or queue binding isn&#39;t set up in RabbtMQ. Since your crawler beans 
&gt; are setting the `exchange` and `routingKey` properties to 
&gt; non-defaults, did you run umbra using the exchange and routing key you 
&gt; defined? If you run umbra with flags as &quot;--exchange heritrix 
&gt; --routing-key phantomjs-domain&quot; before launching the crawl, it should 
&gt; create the needed exchange and queue binding for you. Similarly, the 
&gt; defaults of umbra and Heritrix align, so, if you don&#39;t care about 
&gt; setting those properties differently, you could leave the `exchange` 
&gt; and `routingKey` properties out of the crawler beans and start umbra 
&gt; with the defaults before the crawl is launched, and it should create 
&gt; the default &#39;umbra&#39; exchange and  &#39;urls&#39; queue with appropriate 
&gt; binding automatically.
&gt;
